Description: Sherd of pottery open vessel body, orientation uncertain; offsets at top and bottom of sherd; reserved on offsets, the rest black glazed with; incised and painted decoration in white and yellow; egg and dart pattern.
Curator's comments: More akin to West Slope ware than anything South Italian, though parallels for the motifs are not apparent. On broken edge 'HERA' in pencil; scratched on interior 'DIOSK'.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (ID.019)
